Package com.diffplug.common.rx

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IObservable<T>
    An object which can be supplied in an Observable form.
    Rx.HasRxExecutor
    Marker interface which allows an Executor to specify its own Scheduler.
    RxBox<T>
    RxGetter and Nullable combined in one.
    RxGetter<T>
    Represents a value which can be accessed through a traditional get() method or by listening to its IObservable.
    RxTracingPolicy
    Interface which gets called for every subscription through the Rx mechanism, allowing various kinds of tracing.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Immutables
    Utilties for manipulating Guava's immutable collections.
    Rx<T>
    Rx is a class which unifies the listener models of rx.Observable with com.google.common.util.concurrent.ListenableFuture.
    Rx.RxExecutor
    This class holds an instance of Executor (for ListenableFuture) and Scheduler (for Observable).
    RxBox.Default<T>
    The default implementation of an RxBox.
    RxConversions  
    RxConversions.OnMultiple
    Functions which implement the onMultiple function required by the conversions.
    RxList<T>
    An extension of RxBox>, with convenience methods for modifying the list.
    RxMap<K,V>
    An extension of RxBox>, with convenience methods for modifying and observing the map.
    RxOptional<T>
    An extension of RxBox>, with convenience methods for converting it to an RxSet.
    RxOrderedSet<T>
    An RxList which guarantees to never have any duplicates.
    RxSet<T>
    An extension of RxBox>, with convenience methods for modifying and observing the set, as well as for converting it into an RxBox>.
    RxTracingPolicy.LogSubscriptionTrace
    An RxTracingPolicy which records the stack trace of every subscription which matches its predicate.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    RxOrderedSet.OnDuplicate
    Policies for disallowing duplicates.
